.TH "cdev_add" 9 "cdev_add" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cdev_add \- add a char device to the system
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" cdev_add
.BI "(struct cdev *p "  ","
.BI "dev_t dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "p" 12
the cdev structure for the device
.IP "dev" 12
the first device number for which this device is responsible
.IP "count" 12
the number of consecutive minor numbers corresponding to this
device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBcdev_add\fP adds the device represented by \fIp\fP to the system, making it
live immediately.  A negative error code is returned on failure.
